cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a method for optimizing multi-class classification using vector-valued decision trees within the framework of AdaBoost.MH. This involves optimizing the multi-class edge without reducing the problem to binary one-against-all classifications. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the following sub-categories: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning)
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence)
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition)
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms)
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing)
